				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Born and raised as part of the Independent Fundamental Baptist church, she was told with the other congregants that they must not associate with members of other Baptist denominations and evangelicals, and subscribe to insular marriages within the church, subservience for women, and highly unusual child-raising practices. In her book, <i>I Fired God</i>, Zichterman systematically details the IFB’s disturbing history, exposing a cult-like atmosphere of corruption, greed, and abuse.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Zichterman is currently an abuse advocate and whistleblower fighting against the IFB Church, and was a critical source for the ABC News <i>20/20</i> investigative hour <i>Shattered Faith</i> as well sa the “Ungodly Discipline” series featured on CNN’s <i>Anderson Cooper 360</i>. She also has been a source for <i>The New York Times</i> and <i>Huffington Post</i>.</p>
