				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Helen Wan is Associate General Counsel at the Time Inc. division of Time Warner, where she advises the Lifestyle portfolio of brands and Time Home Entertainment Inc. Before that, she practiced corporate law and entertainment law at firms in New York City. Wan is Co-Chair of Time Inc.’s Asian Pacific American Affinity Group and a frequent public speaker on advancing diversity in the legal profession, success strategies for women and minorities in the corporate workplace, and balancing career with other creative pursuits. She has spoken at law firms, law schools, colleges and universities, bar association conferences and professional networking events, and to corporate Diversity &amp; Inclusion teams.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Wan’s first novel, <i>The Partner Track, </i>about a young Chinese-American woman up for partner at a prestigious global law firm, and about how outsider status and politics complicate her ascent up the corporate ladder, will be published by St. Martin’s Press in September 2013. <i>The Partner Track</i> has ben selected by Amherst College to be its “Amherst Reads” Book Selection for November 2013.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Wan’s essays and reviews of fiction have been published in <i>The Washington Post</i> and elsewhere. Born in California and raised near Washington, D.C., she is a graduate of Amherst College and the University of Virginia School of Law. She lives in New York with her husband and young son.</p>
