				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Botsman writes, speakers, and consults on the power of collaboration and sharing through network technologies, as well as how it will transform business, consumerism, and the way we live, work and consume. In 2010, TIME Magazine called collaborative consumption one of the “10 Ideas That Will Change the World.” She is the founder of <a href="http://cclab.collaborativeconsumption.com/">Collaborative Lab</a>, which helps businesses and governments worldwide to understand and harness the power and potential of collaborative consumption.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Her articles on the relationship between technology and human behavior have been published in Harvard Business Review, The Economist, CNN, New York Times, and other publications. Botsman is also a contributing editor for WIRED UK and has a tech trends column in the Australian Financial Review.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Recently, Botsman was named a 2013 Young Global Leader by the World Economic Forum, an honor that recognizes individuals for their achievements and commitment to improving the state of the world.</p>
