				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Award-winning author Frederick Kaufman has discussed food culture, food politics, and global food justice on NBC and MSNBC, Fox Business News, Bloomberg TV, C-SPAN, and the BBC World Service, along with numerous appearances on <i>NPR</i>. As a contributing editor at Harper’s magazine, Kaufman’s magazine work has also appeared in <i>Scientific American, Nature, Popular Science, The New York Times Sunday Magazine, The New Yorker, Foreign Policy, Gourmet, Saveur, Slate, and Wired</i>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>He is the Professor of English and Journalism at the CUNY Graduate School of Journalism, and has spoken at TEDxManhattan, the James Beard Foundation, the American Museum of Natural History, the New York Public Library, San Francisco’s Commonwealth Club, Yale Sustainable Food, Harvard Law School, and the General Assembly of the United Nations.</p>
